18/02/2011
BELGRADE, Serbia -- Serbia expects that the International Commission on Missing Persons (ICMP) will be actively involved in investigating human organs trafficking allegations, the head of Serbia's committee for missing people, Veljko Odalovic, said on Thursday (February 17th). 
He was speaking at a press conference after talks with ICMP Director General Kathryne Bomberger. 
Odalovic recalled that about 14,000 people in the region remain missing since the 1990s wars and says Serbia is providing all documents and information at its disposal, as well as conducting or assisting with exhumations. 
(RTRS, Beta, Blic - 17/02/11)
